Q: By himself, Jack can clean a yacht in 12 hours. On a particular day, he happens to finish two-thirds of the work. The remaining portion of the work is done by Jill, whose rate of cleaning is just 5% of what Jack can do. How long does it take Jill to finish the remaining work?
Options: (a) 4 (b) 8 (c) 22 (d) 50 (e) 20
A:
Jack alone can clean the yacht in 12 hours. Two-thirds of the work = 2/3 * 12 = 8 hours. Remaining work = 1 - 2/3 = 1/3. Jill can clean 1/3 of the remaining work in 5% of the time taken by Jack = 1/3 * 5% = 1/60 = 20 hours. So the answer is (e).

