Q: The difference between simple interest and C.I. at the same rate for Rs.5000 for 2 years in Rs.72. The rate of interest is?
Options: (a) 10% (b) 12% (c) 6% (d) 8% (e) 4%
A:
Skipping the batch
Skipping the batch
The difference between simple interest and C.I. at the same rate for Rs.5000 for 2 years is given as Rs.72. Let the rate of interest be r%.

Simple interest = Principal x Rate x Time = Rs.5000 x r x 2 = Rs.10000
Compound interest = Principal x (1 + r)^2 x Time = Rs.5000 x (1 + r)^2 x 2 = Rs.7200

So, the rate of interest is (72 - 100) / 5000 = -8%.

