Options: (a) 10!/3 (b) 10!/6 (c) 10!/2 (d) 10!/4 (e) 10!/5
A:
The order of speakers is important. Hence, the number of ways to hold the meeting = 10!/(3!*7!) = 10!/3 = 10/3 = 3. So the answer is (b).

