Q: M = abc is a three digit number and N = cba, if M > N and M - N + 396c = 990. Then how many values of M are more than 300.
Options: (a) 20 (b) 30 (c) 40 (d) 200 (e) None
A:
Let M = xyz and N = cba. Since M > N, M - N + 396c = 990. Now, expanding the left hand side, we get: xyz - cba + 396c = 990. Now, comparing the coefficients of x, y and z, we get: x > 180, y > 180 and z > 180. So, there are only 20 options of M that are more than 300. So the answer is (a).

