Q: A club consists of members whose ages are in A.P. The common difference being 3 months. If the youngest member of the club is just 7 years old and the sum of the ages of all the members is 250, then number of members in the club are :
Options: (a) 18 (b) 20 (c) 25 (d) 26 (e) 27
A:
Let the age of the youngest member be x. Then the age of the next member is x + 3, and so on. The sum of the ages of all the members is given as 250. Hence, we can write an equation: x + (x + 3) + (x + 6) + ... + (x + 2n) = 250. Since the ages are in A.P., we can write: x + (x + 3) + (x + 6) + ... + (x + 2n) = n(x + 3) where n is the number of members in the club. Now, n = 18. So, the answer is (a).

